<td>19</td>
<td>72</td>
<td>40</td>
<td>85</td>
<td>51</td>
<td>113</td>
<td>60</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>55</td>
<td>4</td>
<td>65</td>
<td>22</td>
<td>73</td>
<td>42</td>
<td>87</td>
<td>52</td>
<td>122</td>
<td>61</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>58</td>
<td>6</td>
<td>66</td>
<td>24</td>
<td>75</td>
<td>43</td>
<td>88</td>
<td>53</td>
<td>126</td>
<td>62</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>59</td>
<td>9</td>
<td>67</td>
<td>25</td>
<td>76</td>
<td>44</td>
<td>90</td>
<td>54</td>
<td>144</td>
<td>63</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>60</td>
<td>10</td>
<td>68</td>
<td>30</td>
<td>77</td>
<td>45</td>
<td>94</td>
<td>55</td>
<td>154</td>
<td>64</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>61</td>
<td>14</td>
<td>69</td>
<td>33</td>
<td>78</td>
<td>46</td>
<td>104</td>
<td>57</td>
<td rowspan="3" colspan="2"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>62</td>
<td>15</td>
<td>70</td>
<td>37</td>
<td>79</td>
<td>48</td>
<td>106</td>
<td>58</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>63</td>
<td>17</td>
<td>71</td>
<td>39</td>
<td>83</td>
<td>49</td>
<td>109</td>
<td>59</td>
</tr>
</table>
</dd>
</dl>
<p>This cdf shows that the minimum value in the subimage is 52 and the maximum value is 154. The cdf of 64 for value 154 coincides with the number of pixels in the image. The cdf must be normalized to <span class="texhtml">[0,255]</span>. The general histogram equalization formula is:</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="
cdf(v) =
 \mathrm{round}
 \left(
   \frac {cdf(v) - cdf_{min}} {(M \times N) - cdf_{min}}
   \times (L - 1)
 \right)
" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/f/d/7fd062f49cc532952412cadafea39afc.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>Where cdf<sub>min</sub> is the minimum value of the cumulative distribution function (in this case 1), M × N gives the image's number of pixels (for the example above 64, where M is width and N the height) and L is the number of grey levels used (in most cases, like this one, 256). The equalization formula for this particular example is:</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="
cdf(v) =
 \mathrm{round}
 \left(
   \frac {cdf(v) - 1} {63}
   \times 255
 \right)
" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/b/5/4b5d7f082f5c8031873ec6c06b3dccab.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>For example, the cdf of 78 is 46. (The value of 78 is used in the bottom row of the 7th column.) The normalized value becomes</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="
cdf(78) =
 \mathrm{round}
 \left(
   \frac {46 - 1} {63}
   \times 255
 \right)
=
 \mathrm{round}
 \left(
   0.714286
   \times 255
 \right)
=
182
" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/2/7/82767c75b0a6c022a832248b09267442.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>Once this is done then the values of the equalized image are directly taken from the normalized cdf to yield the equalized values:</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="
\begin{bmatrix}
   0 &amp;  12 &amp;  53 &amp;  93 &amp; 146 &amp;  53 &amp;  73 &amp; 166 \\
  65 &amp;  32 &amp;  12 &amp; 215 &amp; 235 &amp; 202 &amp; 130 &amp; 158 \\
  57 &amp;  32 &amp; 117 &amp; 239 &amp; 251 &amp; 227 &amp;  93 &amp; 166 \\
  65 &amp;  20 &amp; 154 &amp; 243 &amp; 255 &amp; 231 &amp; 146 &amp; 130 \\
  97 &amp;  53 &amp; 117 &amp; 227 &amp; 247 &amp; 210 &amp; 117 &amp; 146 \\
 190 &amp;  85 &amp;  36 &amp; 146 &amp; 178 &amp; 117 &amp;  20 &amp; 170 \\
 202 &amp; 154 &amp;  73 &amp;  32 &amp;  12 &amp;  53 &amp;  85 &amp; 194 \\
 206 &amp; 190 &amp; 130 &amp; 117 &amp;  85 &amp; 174 &amp; 182 &amp; 219 
\end{bmatrix}
" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/2/1/3/21348c07d20f6fb0e64d7e27c1a269d2.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>Notice that the minimum value (52) is now 0 and the maximum value (154) is now 255.</p>
<dl>
<dd>
<table>
<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/File:JPEG_example_subimage.svg" class="image" title="JPEG example subimage.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/JPEG_example_subimage.svg/200px-JPEG_example_subimage.svg.png" width="200" height="200" border="0" /></a></td>
<td><a href="/wiki/File:JPEG_example_subimage_-_equalized.svg" class="image" title="JPEG example subimage - equalized.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/JPEG_example_subimage_-_equalized.svg/200px-JPEG_example_subimage_-_equalized.svg.png" width="200" height="200" border="0" /></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">Original</td>
<td align="center">Equalized</td>
</tr>
</table>
</dd>
</dl>
